english:
  title: Settling Your Fate
  author: Lee Na
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The north wind howls and snow swirls wildly—
    Thinking of your trials, my heart grows heavy with sorrow.
    Beauty will ruin the body; guard against it with care.
    Words can wound the self; consider them well before speaking.
    Wild companions bring only waste in the end,
    And pride that scorns others brings harm to oneself.
    Seek nothing beyond loyalty and filial duty in all things,
    And your good name will shine before the king.
